-- China c.bank governor says to increase yuan's flexibility
-- By Kevin Yao
-- Thu Jul 10, 2014 12:18AM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, July 10 (Reuters) - China's central bank governor Zhou Xiaochuan said on Thursday that the government would increase the flexibility of the yuan currency and reduce market intervention.

He was speaking on the sidelines of annual high-level talks between China and the United States.